inn1.comm: straightaway off the mark and a very risky single too, Gambhir taps it softly to Patel at short midwicket and takes off, he takes aim and the throw at the stumps is just a little too wide
well the first signs of low bounce, after the ball left Sehwag it bounced very low to Prior and rebounded off him
pitches on a good length outside off and beats the outside edge, Anderson will be happy with that bounce
softly tucked away very close to the pads to the on side and they jog the single very easily this time
oh an inside edge, Sehwag hangs his bat out outside off the ball trickles past the stumps and runs to fine leg, should have been two there
pitches around the off stumps and goes through a little low to Prior
good bounce and carry for Broad early on, lands outside off and Sehwag safely lets it go

inside edge and timber! Broad gets the ball to cut back in after pitching on a good length and Sehwag is a little late in covering the movement, the ball takes the inside edge and strikes the base of the offstump. Sehwag played a similar shot off Anderson in the previous over but got away. Not this time.
Appeal Straightaway, pitches just a shade outside leg and hits his pad possibly outside the leg as well, Broad was super confident
oof, the low bouce again, Raina does well to bend down and pat it away, ominous signs there
once again the bounce isn;t that great, Raina gets behind the line and defends it away
that should ease the nerves, Broad angles it a little wide outside off and Raina gets his bat nicely behind it and drives with the movement, bisects the gap between cover and mid-off
hits a good length outside off, he gets across and pushes it to the off side
just back of a length on middle stump, he turns his wrists and whips it down to square leg
continues over the wicket, he adjusts to a fuller length, clips it away with wase close to his pads and beats square leg
dead straight and in line with the off stump, he shuffles across just a touch and defends solidly down the pitch
loses his line and strays too wide outside the off stump, Saheba stretches his hands
hits a good length outside leg and comes across the left hander, he gets behind it and defends
gets across his stumps to a good length delivery and defends softly towards mid-off, thinks of a single

edged! Well like i said earlier there isn't too much bounce on this pitch, he pitches it outside off and gets it to swing late, he hangs his bat out and the outside edge falls well short of first slip and runs away for four
tapped towards midwicket for a quick single and that's 1000 runs in a calendar year for Gambhir, well done GG!
good length outside off, pushed to the packed off side field

very soft dismissal and Broad has two now, the ball pitches on a good length on middle and leg, Raina expects it to come on quicker and is too early on the stroke, he ends up chipping it tamely to Patel at short square leg who falls forward and takes it comfortably
fullish outside off, he safely pushes it to the off side
tucks it close to his pads and a misfield at midwickwet allows him to get off the mark
full and searching for the late inswing, he meets the ball with an angled bat and taps it to short cover
was that a drop? Tough one for Prior, he plays it too early and hangs his bat outside off, the inside edge travels quickly to Prior's left and he dives and just manages to get a glove to it
fullish and angling away outside off, he gets forward and pushes it to third man
strays on the pads, he nudges it down to fine leg and the fielder was fielding a little too square for that, the outfield carries it through to the fence quickly
hits a good length outside off, he gets forward and pushes it down the pitch
he catches gambhir fishing outside the off stump and nearly gets him to edge it, there was just a tinge of away movement
hits a good length on middle and leg, he taps it to the on side
good length outside off, he taps it towards point
tucked away firmly off his pads, Samit Patel does well at midwicket to slide and cut it off
slower ball outside leg, he shuffles across his stumps and works it behind square on the on side

Appeal Rohit gets a ball that keeps a little low and manages to pat it away very close to his pads, Broad reckoned it was pad first and went up in appeal, Tiffen was unmoved, there was no pad on it anyway
pushed to cover
gets across his stumps to a good length delivery and taps it down to packed short cover cordon
short of a length on middle and leg, he merely shuffles just a touch and clips it away deftly down to fine leg, he knows the fielder is very square
pitches outside leg and comes back in, he nudges it to the on side
pitches on a good length outside off and seams away, he safely lets it go to Prior
pitches outside off and just shapes away, a mere defensive push is enough to beat backward point, Bell does well to sprint and slide near the boundary to cut it off
lunges forward and pushes it to the off side
pushed back to the bowler
slides on the pads, he nudges it softly to the on side

He's thrown his wicket away, a sudden rush of blood from Rohit Sharma, he attempts to hook a short ball on a slow pitch and fails to carry off the stroke, Owais Shah at midwicket takes a sitter, Broad is the star of the morning
Good morning Mr Yuvraj! Gets quite a nasty bouncer to start off and he does well to sway away from it, Broad's on fire this morning
strays on the pads, he tucks it away off his hips and gets a leg bye
pitches on the line of offstump, he gets behind the line and defends
Good start for Flintoff straightaway, gets it to pitch on the channel outside off and hold its line, he fishes at it
well that caught Yuvraj in a real tangle, the ball is banged in short of a length and doesn't bounce as much as expected, Yuvraj lets it go and realises that it wasn't too far from his glove
hits a good length outside off, he pushes it down the pitch
lands outside off and holds its line before reaching Prior
he oversteps and strays off line as well, it's down the leg side and Yuvraj works it on its way easily past the keeper and down to fine leg
Free Hit: That's a tee off! Flintoff pitches it on a good length and the bounce is good enough for Yuvraj to stay at the crease and club it high over midwicket
full outside off, defended to the off side
just a touch wide outside off, he tries to glide it past backward point but can't beat the fielder
taps it just wide of the diving short cover fielder and sets off in a flash, excellent running by Gambhir
cranks up the pace and hits a good length outside off, he safely let s it go
a harsh call, it wasn't too wide outside off and Broad is clearly unhappy with Tiffen's call, Pietersen has a word with the umpire
pitches on middle and leg, he tucks it to midwicket
slower ball outside off, the ball keeps very low to Prior, this pitch is on the slower side no doubt
pitches outside off, he gets well forward and steers it to point
pitches on off and middle and gambhir waits patiently for the ball to come to him before tapping it back to the bowler
full and angling across the left hander, he lunges forward and steers it to deep point
comes round the wicket and the change of angle nearly works, he catches Yuvraj prodding outside off and nearly gets an edge
this time he gets well forward and some wood on it
gets forward to a full delivery and pushes it off the meat of the bat past the infield on the off side, Bell's there at sweeper cover to cut it off
hits a good length outside off and holds its line before reaching Prior
not a very good start for Harmison, he strays on the pads and he clips it off his pads and beats Prior, the fielder is square so it's a four as soon as it beats the keeper
pitches around the off stump, he plays it square on the off side
good length outside off, he pushes it to mid-off
angles across the left hander and Yuvraj lets it go, once again the ball dips to Prior after pitching, keeping certainly isn't easy on a slow pitch
pitches outside off, he shoulders arms
tries to clip it behind square on the leg side but the ball skids through a lot quicker and clips his pads, Harmison appeals optimistically but gets no support
gets forward and steers it square of the wicket on the off side for a single
plays a little too early and hangs his bat out to cut, luckily for him the inside edge thuds on to his boot
pitches outside off and holds its line, he decides not to chase it
Flintoff again tempts him to drive outside off but Yuvraj doesn't oblige, India are under pressure and need to be cautious
adjusts his line closer to the off stump, he lunges forward and pushes it to sweeper cover
steers it with an angled bat square on the off side, that off side ring is packed
poor cricket all round, strays wide outside off, he chases it as well
shapes to drive a full delivery through the covers but gets an inside edge which rolls to the on side
bangs it in on a good length outside off and gets it to shape away, he tries to glide it through the off side but Bell's there at backward point to intercept it
good length on middle and leg, he tucks it away down to mid-on
clips it to the on side and searches for that gap but can't beat midwicket
full and slides wide outside off, he pushes it to mid-off
improvisation par excellence, he advances down the pitch early and clips it high over midwicket, that's a sign of confidence and Gambhir has loads of it
left alone outside off
safe, Flintoff lands it on a good length outside off, Yuvraj waits on it and glides it very late wide of first slip, there were shades of Arjuna Ranatunga in that shot
pitches outside off, he safely lets it go
teases him outside off, he safely shoulders arms
this time he gets the ball to bend back in off the same length, he draws Yuvraj on the forward prod and he safely pushes it away
waltzes down the track and pushes a full toss to long-on, Shah fumbles
flighted outside off, he defends
pushed in quicker through the air, he works it to long-on
much shorter in length and outside off, he makes room and cuts to sweeper cover
fuller in length and pitching on middle and off, he defends
Patel strays down the leg side and pays the price, Yuvraj deftly glides it wide of the fielder at short fine leg, he knows where the fielders are

superb timing, Gambhir clips it gently off his pads and honestly it didnt seem like a boundary as it left the bat, the outfield is so quick that the fielder at fine leg had to dive in despair at deep square leg to cut it off
nudged to the on side
comes round the wicket to Gambhir, lunges forward and pushes it to the off side
bangs it in short, he turns the face of the bat and and fends it to the on side and sets off quickly
that's a half volley outside off and Gambhir merely pushed it in to the arc between mid-off and cover, super timing and placement, a minimal backlift was enough
gets forward and defends to mid-off
comes over the wicket, gets forward and defends down the track
full in length, he gets well forward and pushes it towards mid-on
tucks it away softly down to deep square leg and sets off very quickly, they take a chance with Shah's arm and complete the second comfortably
chips it uppishly down to backward point, cries of 'catch it' from Prior
lunges forward and taps it away very softly in front of mid-off and gets off the blocks quickly, another well-judged run
slower ball, the off cutter, he turns the face of the bat and clips it to midwicket
pushed to midwicket
pushes it quicker through the air, he forces it back to the bowler
slower through the air, he works it to the on side
gives it more flight, Yuvraj waits at the crease, gets on his knee and thumps it high over midwicket, a couple of bounces and four
tucked to the on side
flighted down leg and turned behind square on the on side
full on the pads and pushed through the line to long-on, Bopara does the fielding
the slower ball, pitches outside leg and hits his pad as he tries to clip it to the on side, Collingwood appeals for an lbw
slides on the pads and he gets some wood on it and beats midwicket
another slower ball, pitches outside leg and clips him low on the pad, Collingwood appeals confidently again, you can't give those out
bowls that off cutter again, pushed to the off side
the slower ones get a little too repetitive and Yuvraj takes him to task, he stays at the crease, fetches it from the off stump and tees off, the ball sails over the straight boundary
tucked to the on side and they take the first run very quickly, another example of the understanding between this pair
comes over the wicket, he waltzes down the track, checks his stroke and clips it wide of midwicket for a couple
brings himself forward and clips a full toss from outside off down to midwicket
fullish outside off, he pushes it with the angle to the on side
holds the length back and pitches it wide outside off, he makes room and slices it down to point
stays at the crease, waits for the turn before tucking it towards midwicket to keep the strike
flighted on middle and leg, he pushes it down towards mid-on
the slow off cutter, he waits on it and clips it late down to square leg
the off cutter again, he chips it uppishly towards short midwicket and thinks of a single
the offcutter turns in to a full toss and Yuvraj very elegantly clips it over midwicket almost on one leg, that's style for you
pitches outside off, he glides it down to backward point
clips an offcutter on his pads to square leg
comes over the wicket, lands outside off and he steers it to backward point
slightly slower in pace, lands on middle and leg and he clips it behind square on the on side
gets his high backlift down and taps it just wide of cover and sets off in a flash
slowish delivery just wide outside off, he gets well forward and glides it wide of backward point
fullish outside off and pushed through the line towards long-on
they're taking the singles very easily, he tucks it down to midwicket with soft hands and jogs the single
on a good length and thats turned straight to midwicket
there it is, his 13th half-century, tucked off his pads past square leg for a single and Indore cheers its appreciation, a good knock but plenty to do still
whips a single between midwicket and square leg
on the stumps and deflected wide of square leg for two, Pietersen came in and was slow to react, there was some indecision and Gambhir pounced on it
tight line and length, turned straight to short square leg
walks away to about a fifth or sixth stump, dangerously exposing all the sticks, and uppishly cuts a single in front of backward point, he's growing in confidence
rotates the strike well, tucking one off the stumps with ease

shot! What a way to get to fifty, all powerful wrists in that shot, back leg going up and bat coming down over a full ball excellently, clipping that past midwicket and mid-on for a sumptuous boundary
comes forward and drives a single into the covers now
short one and he gets back to pull a couple past midwicket
pitches on a length and Gambhir turns it away towards mid-on
squared up and edges this one, Harmison pitches on a length and draws a loose defensive, the ball squirts down past where slips could have been

slow delivery pitches outside leg stump, short, Yuvraj sees it and gets down to swat it away, misses and gets hit on the pad, Collingwood doesn't do much but Prior starts to appeal before realising it couldn't have been given out
comes forward and drives right to cover
shuffles and works this one off middle and leg for a single
short of a length on leg stump and tucked towards midwicket
too straight and he flicks comfortably wide of midwicket
pitches on middle and leg and Yuvraj turns to the fielder
pitches it full and wide outside off, he gets forward and steers it to sweeper cover
commits early to a forward punch but checks his stroke and softly pushes it to cover
too short, you can't bowl that length on this pitch, Yuvraj almost anticipates the length early and clubs it high over midwicket, one bounce and four
he's brave enough to attempt another short ball but it's a slower ball, Yuvraj tries to club it over midwicket again but checks his stroke, he places it to long-on
full outside off and steers it wide of backward point
angles it wide of the off stump, he hangs his bat out and steers it down to third man
fullish outside off and pushed to long-off
dead straight, don't even fetch it, pitches on a fullish length on middle and off, he gets his bat right behind the ball and caresses it past the bowler and mid-on, he's got elegance and grace
lovely delivery, the offcutter beats him on the forward prod, the stumping's been referred to the third umpire
nudged down to short fine leg for a single
tries to work it off his pads and he finds the fielder
gets his wrists working and clips it away down to deep square leg
well he's just milking the bowling, full and wide outside off and he easily glides it down to third man
loss of concentration as Yuvraj chases a wide one outside off, it was there to be hit alright there was no foot movement to go with it
angles it down to sweeper cover for a single
comes round the wicket, he pushes it to the off side
You can't keep Yuvraj quiet, Broad commits the sin of banging it in short and al Yuvraj had to do was to smash it high over midwicket's outstretched arms
full outside off and steered to the deep on the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he tucks it down to squre leg
makes room, uses his feet but can't beat Collingwood at short cover who does well to cut it off
take that! He waltzes down the track, lofts with the turn and scoops it high over deep extra cover, it was an inside out shot executed to perfection
tries to nudge it down to fine leg and nearly gets a feather tough to it, Prior is very confident and appeals for a catch, Russell Tiffen is unmoved
tucked to square leg

the bowling change has worked! Gambhir walks across his stumps and tries to fetch it from outside the off stump and work it to the on side, he tries to clip it away but gets an inside edge which rolls on to his stumps
comes round the wicket, aims for the yorker length and he digs it out to sweeper cover
lands outside the off stumps and gets a bit of lateral movement inwards before reaching the keeper
pitches it full and gets a bit of late inswing, Dhoni is watchful enough to cover the line and drive it to the off side
holds the length back but gets the same amount of inward movement, he taps it back to the bolwer
adjusts his line to outside the off stump, he safely shoulders arms
persists with that length outside off, it seems to be working as Dhoni is cramped for room and hence can't squeeze a single
defended back to the bowler
beats him with a brute of an offcutter, well bowled
defended back to the bowler
his line goes astray and he delivers that wide down the leg side, he gets on his knee and sweeps it fine
flighted outside off, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
flighted outside off, he gets forward and pushes it to mid-off and sets off, there's an overthrow and they steal an extra run
pitches outside off, pushed to the off side
gets on the backfoot and taps it away with soft hands just wide of point and sets off for a run quickly
angling away from the left hander, Yuvraj goes on the backfoot and defends it to the off side
angles away from the left hander again, he misses out on the cut and the ball bounces low to Prior, another sign of low bounce
holds the length back outside off, he takes a single to the off side
angling across the left hander, he pokes is bat out and confidently glides it past slip and backward point to reach the boundary
defended to the off side
gets across his stumps and tucks it to square leg and sets off, Yuvraj is circumspect but they complete the single
lands on middle and leg, he defends to the on side
defends back to the bowler
turns the face of the bat and glances it to backward square leg
back of a length delivery on the middle and leg, Yuvraj goes on the backfoot and pulls it away to deep mid wicket
bangs it in short, he swivels and pulls it down to fine leg
hits a good length outside off, he offers the full face of the bat and steers it wide of cover

brilliant commitment by Stuart Broad, when Dhoni nudged it down to fine leg a boundary seemed certain but Broad had other ideas, diving his right and mopping up just inches before the rope, KP applauded that as well, btw Dhoni goes past 1000 runs in the calendar year
pushed to gully
gets on the backfoot and defends back to the bowler
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
gets down the sweep too early and fails to make contact with the bat
gets on the backfoot and steers it to deep backward point
on the middle and leg, Dhoni goes on the backfoot and defends it on the leg side
flighted on middle and leg, he tries to glance it fine but the ball clips his pads and rolls away
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
comes over the wicket, he drives past the diving Patel and works it down to long-off
flighted on middle and leg, he tucks it to the on side
gets forward and defends with soft hands
flighted outside off, he gets forward and defends
flighted outside off, he defends to the off side
brute force, the ball lands on a fullish length on middle and off and he plays a feisty straight drive back past the bowler, nobody moved, they didn't have to
gets on the front foot and defends to the off side
flighted on middle and leg, he nudges it to deep backward square leg
cuts to the off side
defended back to the bowler
flighted on middle and leg, glanced to fine leg
gets down the track and defends to the on side
waits for it at the crease and punches it hard down to long-off, he's on 99
too short on this pitch, Dhoni made use of the width on offer and rocked on the back foot and slapped it past exytra cover, the fielder had no chance
gets on his knee early to sweep but fails to make contact with the bat
pushes it down the track and takes the single
that's back to back tons for Yuvraj and there's no stopping him! He deftly steers it wide of point and leaps in the air after getting to three figures
temporary respite for England, Dhoni tries to improvise by glancing to third man with very little room outside the off stump, the offcutter nips back in and shaves the off stump
driven to extra cover for a single
hits a good length outside off, he defends to the off side
shuffles across his stumps and gets off the mark with a couple to deep square leg
tests him out with a short one, he hops at the crease and fends it to the off side
short of a length again and angling towards the body, he gets his bat high and nudges it to the on side for a single
gives him plenty of width outside off, he opens the face of the bat and steers it to backward point, Yuvraj refuses the second run
well bowled, stump to stump line, Yuvraj gives him some respect by defending
gets his high backlift down and clips a full delivery to long-on
floated on middle and leg, he tucks it close to his pads and gets off the strike
pushed on the pads, he works it to short fine leg
the offcutter, gets forward early and steers it in front of point and sets off
hits a good length on middle and leg from over the wicket, he closes the face of the bat and taps it towards midwicket
gets across his stumps and steers it wide of square lef
a false stroke from Yuvraj,the ball stops on him and he chips it in front of short midwicket
strays down the leg side, he gets a feather touch to it and glides it wide of the keeper
cuts it wide of backward point and Shah does well in the deep to cut it off
comes over the wicket, slower ball, he strays on the pads and he nudges it in front of short fine leg
well bowled, he fires in the yorker and he can only jam it back to the bowler
excellent stuff from Flintoff, he makes run scoring impossible by firing in another yorker, he fields well off his own bowling too
overpitches just a touch and he smashes it hard and low down to long-on, there's protection there
Flintoff cannot get the yorker going to Yuvraj, he bangs it short instead and Yuvraj swivels and pulls past square leg
overpitches on the pads and he clubs it over mid-on
slower ball outside the off stump, he steers it to short third man and sets off
wide outside off, wasted delivery
lovely incoming delivery, he shapes to cut but misses
wide outside the offstump, he makes room and carves it over backward point
and finally England have found a way to dismiss Yuvraj, Broad pitches it up outside off and Yuvraj throws everything at it, there's a feather touch and Prior takes the offering easily
slower delivery outside off, he steers it down to short third man and they take an extra run off a misfield, Bell does the chasing
pushed towards cover for a quick single and a direct hit would have sent Harbhajan packing
Flighted outside off pushed to cover
Dances down the track, fails to put it away
Brilliant stop! That really traveled off the bat and looked to be heading towards long-on but Flintoff got his left hand to it and saved 3 runs
flighted on  middle and leg and he slog sweeps that over deep midwicket
sweeps to short fine leg, opportunity for a run out but the throw was way too high for Prior to gather it and break the stumps
pitches on middle and leg, he turns it to deep square leg
sloppy stuff from England, Pathan heaves it along the ground to midwicket, Bopara fumbles first and Anderson slides as well but doesn't time his dive properly
pitched outside off and steered wide of point for a single
bangs it in short and he swivels and pulls down to fine leg, the fielder is fairly square

goes for an across the line swat but gets an inside edge onto his body, he takes a quick single and Pathan nearly collides with Broad who falls over, no physical contact there so all well! Remember Watson and Gambhir?
goes for another heave and this time he takes a couple
makes plenty of room to carve it through the off side but he hits the full toss straight to cover
excellent length, lands on the blockhole and he can only heave it along the turf to midwicket

direct hit, he makes room and clubs a full delivery straight to Pietersen at mid-off who's back on the edge of the circle, he takes aim and knocks the stumps at the bowler's end and Harbhajan doesn't even wait for the umpire's signal, he walks
another yorker, superbly bowled and he can't put it away
digs in another one of the blockhole and he can only squeeze it out to the packed off side field within the circle
low full toss angling towards the pads and he takes a single to midwicket
well bowled there, bangs it in short outside off, the ball angles towards zaheer and he decides against the stroke
bangs in the bouncer and he can't make contact with the pull, the umpire signals the one bouncer for the over
this is good testing stuff fom Broad, walks down the track to club him down the track but he fails to get bat on ball off another bouncer
the slower ball and once again Zaheer swings in complete desperation and fails to make contact
dug out back to the bowler

well for a change there's some wood on leather and it beats the bowler, he pushes it to Patel at mid-on and sets off for a very risky run, he hits the timber, no need for the replay, Zaheer's misery ends
that swing spoils what was otherwise an excellent over by Broad, he overpitches on the pads and he swings it high over deep midwicket
yorker on the pads, he gets off the strike
inswinging yorker on middle and leg, he digs it out to long-on
another yorker on the leg stump, he shuffles and squeezes it out behind square on the on side
pitches close to the base of the middle stump, he makes room and plays it hard down to long-off
holds the length back and cuts square of the wicket on the off side, third man mops up
inswinger on the base of the pads, he makes room and pushes it wide of midwicket for a single
makes room to heave it over midwicket but misses, Harmison bowls it bang on the leg stump line, the ball goes through straight and pegs the legstump back
he makes room and misses, the ball creeps past the legstump, Pathan was off in a flash, Munaf was too slow off the blocks
Harmison commits the crime of bowling a length ball at this stage, Yusuf Pathan makes room and clubs this high over long-on
and again! Obviously Harmison hasn't learnt from his mistake, another length ball, this time further down the legstump and he heaves it over deep square leg
fuller and this time wide outside off, he makes room and scoops it over point, nobody patrolling the boundary, that's four
And Yusuf Pathan celebrates his 26th birthday with his maiden ODI fifty! He clips it down to deep square leg, a ballistic knock off just 29 balls, well done

inn2.comm: just the one slip in place, lands outside off and slants away slightly, left alone
pitches around middle and leg, doesn't exert himself much, he softly taps it wide of midwicket to get the innings off the mark
if you stray on the pads then pay up, too easy for Prior as he waits for the ball and glances it down to fine leg, the outfield does the rest
better line and length, much straighter, he's solid in defense
strays towards the leg side but he nudges it square on the on side, fine leg picks it up

athleticism at its best and Raina is the toast of the team at the moment, Bell taps it with soft hands in front of Raina at short mid-off and sets off confidently, the ball goes across Raina but it doesn't hinder his dive as he slides and in one motion under arms the ball at the stumps, there's no need for a replay, Bell was miles out of his crease
bangs it in short and he evades the bouncer easily
edged and it doesn't carry, he tries to defend it but the ball keeps low and travels quickly off the outside edge and rolls past first slip
gets nicely behind the line and defends on the front foot
holds the length back outside the off stump and he gets a long way across his stumps and defends back to the bowler
pitches around the offstump line and gets behind the line and defends again
angles it towards middle and leg, he shuffles just a touch and taps it back to the bowler
lands around the off and middle stump line, gets across and pats it back to the bowler
the slower ball, he shuffles across and tries to drive straight but he meets the ball on an angle and hence finds mid-on
angles it wide of the right hander and he uses the movement to glide it down to third man
fuller in length, he gets his front pad across his stumps and defends to the off side
angles it straight and towards the pads, he uses his wrists and works it to fine leg
just gives him a fraction of width outside off and he punches it off the middle of the bat wide of extra cover, Raina sprints and pulls it back
lovely shot, full and straight from Munaf, he merely drives through the line and beats the bowler and mid-on comfortably
holds the length back outside off, he gets across and taps it in front of cover
bowls a good line and length outside off, he tries to punch it on the front foot but mistimes the drive
well that extra bounce there, catches Shah by surprise but he plays it with soft hands and fends it off his gloves
hits a good length on the off stump, he defends
closes the face of the bat and knocks it softly down to short mid-on and sets off, he makes his ground though the throw was just wide of the stumps
gets forward and defends a fullish delivery back to the bowler
fuller in length and he drives the ball harder, mid-off picks it up
in the length to drive but he pushes it straight to mid-off, England need to push on here
full in length again, no swing for zaheer, he pats it back to the bowler
gives him width outside off and Shah slashes and misses, he's trying to break free
holds the length back a little and he pats it back down the pitch, that's a maiden by Zaheer
bowls a dead straight line, hardly any room for him to cut loose, he settles for a defensive push back to the bowler
holds the length back outside off, he taps it to point
